  <div class="panel-heading">Dave "Sub-Zero" Johnson</div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>
      An original member of the Dee Park Basketball League, Dave Johnson was taken from us suddenly in August 2010. He was a friend to all with an infectious smile often heard yelling, "Who authorized that?" after some ill advised three point shot was taken. He picked up the nickname "Sub-Zero" as he tended to stay in ball games for extended periods. A solid rebounder who looked to distribute the ball he could also score in bunches. By far his most long lasting effect upon many of us is the long standing friendships he built with so many of us. It was an honor and blessing to call you friend, brother and teammate. You cast a giant shadow Dave, I am so glad we share the hope of heaven! 
    </p>
